Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.17,0:02:08.14,辉注,,0,0,0,,氧气：黄色/红色\N氮气：蓝色
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.02,0:00:02.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,本视频由Blinkist赞助
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.02,0:00:02.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,This video is supported by Blinkist.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.20,0:00:10.34,辉注,,0,0,0,,Challenging Minisatellite Payload, CHAMP: 挑战性小卫星有效载荷
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.20,0:00:10.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,2000年 德国一颗名为CHAMP的卫星发射入轨 用于研究地球大气
Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.20,0:00:10.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the year 2000, a German satellite called CHAMP was launched into orbit to study the Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.68,0:00:12.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,当它飞过北极上空时
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.68,0:00:12.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,As it flew over the North Pole,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.50,0:00:17.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,卫星遇到了一个密集的气团 让卫星开始减速
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.50,0:00:17.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,it came across a dense pocket of air which started to slow the satellite down.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.82,0:00:21.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,尽管这个高度大气含量微不足道
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.82,0:00:21.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although the atmosphere is almost non-existent at this altitude,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.46,0:00:25.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,但仍有极少量的大气悬浮在四周
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.46,0:00:25.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,there are still small traces of atmosphere floating around.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.36,0:00:27.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在CHAMP穿越这块气团的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.36,0:00:27.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,But when CHAMP passed through the pocket of air,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:27.95,0:00:32.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,它探测到的空气密度竟然比预期值增加了两倍
Dialogue: 2,0:00:27.95,0:00:32.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,it measured an increase in air density of almost double the expected value.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:32.52,0:00:34.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,科学家们当时并没有意识到此事
Dialogue: 2,0:00:32.52,0:00:34.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Scientists weren't aware at the time,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:34.53,0:00:38.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,但事实上该气团是由极光造成的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:34.53,0:00:38.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,but this pocket of dense air was being caused by an aurora.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.73,0:00:43.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些绚烂的光影在几个世纪以来一直吸引着人类
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.73,0:00:43.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,These dazzling displays of light have fascinated the human race for centuries.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:43.73,0:00:47.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,人们花了几百年才揭开极光的秘密
Dialogue: 2,0:00:43.73,0:00:47.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,Unlocking the mystery of auroras took hundreds of years -
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.34,0:00:50.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,而且科学家们至今还在不断学习
Dialogue: 2,0:00:47.34,0:00:50.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,and today, scientists are still learning more.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.17,0:00:55.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,在北极苔原深处 研究人员正在研究一种不同的极光
Dialogue: 2,0:00:51.17,0:00:55.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,Deep in the Arctic tundra, researchers are studying a different kind of aurora
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.87,0:00:59.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,这种极光正不断导致我们的大气往外太空泄漏
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.87,0:00:59.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is causing our atmosphere to leak into space.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.62,0:01:02.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,关于极光的记录可以追溯到史前壁画
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.62,0:01:02.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,Records of auroras date back to prehistoric paintings -
Dialogue: 1,0:01:02.82,0:01:09.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,但第一次科学观测是在1790年由科学家亨利·卡文迪许进行的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:02.82,0:01:09.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,but the first scientific observation was made in 1790 by scientist Henry Cavendish.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:09.54,0:01:12.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,他使用三角测量法估计极光发生在地球表面上空100公里左右的地方
Dialogue: 2,0:01:09.54,0:01:12.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,He used triangulation to estimate that auroras
Dialogue: 1,0:01:12.45,0:01:17.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,他使用三角测量法估计极光发生在地球表面上空100公里左右的地方
Dialogue: 2,0:01:12.45,0:01:17.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,were taking place around 100 kilometers above the Earth's surface.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.08,0:01:22.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,随着时间的推移 科学家们了解到极光是太阳与地球相互作用的结果
Dialogue: 2,0:01:17.08,0:01:22.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,Over time, scientists learned that auroras are an effect of how the Sun interacts with Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:23.45,0:01:27.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,地球有一个磁场 保护我们免受太阳风的影响
Dialogue: 2,0:01:23.45,0:01:27.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,Earth has a magnetic field which protects us from the Sun's solar wind.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:28.13,0:01:31.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些太阳风是由带电粒子组成的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:28.13,0:01:31.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,These solar winds are made up of charged particles
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.68,0:01:35.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,它们从太阳射出 具有巨大的能量
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.68,0:01:35.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,which shoot out from the sun with enormous amounts of energy.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.64,0:01:41.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,当带电粒子到达地球时 大部分都被我们的磁场挡住了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.64,0:01:41.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,When the charged particles arrive at Earth, most of them are deflected by our magnetic field.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.58,0:01:47.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在南北两极 它们可以偷偷穿过并与我们的大气层发生短暂的相互作用
Dialogue: 2,0:01:41.58,0:01:47.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,But at the North and South poles, they can sneak through and briefly interact with our atmosphere.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:47.69,0:01:53.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,当这些带电粒子碰撞时 它们的能量会转移到我们大气层的粒子中
Dialogue: 2,0:01:47.69,0:01:53.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,These charged particles transfer their energy into the particles of our atmosphere when they collide.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.89,0:01:57.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,这种相互作用会以光的形式释放出能量
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.89,0:01:57.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,This interaction releases energy in the form of light,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.14,0:02:00.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,于是我们就能看到美丽的极光了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.14,0:02:00.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,creating the beautiful display we know as the aurora.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.17,0:02:03.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,粒子根据其类型和传递的能量 会释放出的特定颜色的光
Dialogue: 2,0:02:01.17,0:02:03.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Specific colors of light are released
Dialogue: 1,0:02:03.28,0:02:08.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,粒子根据其类型和传递的能量 会释放出的特定颜色的光
Dialogue: 2,0:02:03.28,0:02:08.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,depending on the type of particle and the amount of energy being transferred.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.61,0:02:12.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,尽管极光所涉及的能量巨大
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.61,0:02:12.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Despite the enormous amounts of energy involved in auroras,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:12.80,0:02:17.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,但粒子很快就会恢复到正常状态 我们的大气层也不会受到伤害
Dialogue: 2,0:02:12.80,0:02:17.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,the particles quickly return to a normal state and our atmosphere is unharmed.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.27,0:02:23.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,有一段时间 科学家们认为氧气分子太重了 无法逃离地球引力
Dialogue: 2,0:02:18.27,0:02:23.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,For a while, scientists believed that oxygen was too heavy to escape Earth's gravity -
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.64,0:02:28.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以当CHAMP在异常高海拔的太空探测到空气团的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.64,0:02:28.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,so when CHAMP discovered pockets of air at unusually high altitudes,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:28.25,0:02:30.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们也不担心氧气会离开地球
Dialogue: 2,0:02:28.25,0:02:30.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,they weren't worried about it leaving Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.14,0:02:35.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,但当科学家开始研究太空中的近地区域时
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.14,0:02:35.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,But when scientists started to study the near Earth regions of space,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.26,0:02:40.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们却发现大量的电离氧 而这只能来自地球
Dialogue: 2,0:02:35.26,0:02:40.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,they found large amounts of ionized oxygen which could only have originated from Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.82,0:02:47.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,出于某种原因 我们大气层中的氧粒子获得了足够的能量 摆脱了地球的引力
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.82,0:02:47.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,Somehow, the oxygen particles in our atmosphere were getting enough energy to escape Earth's gravitational pull.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:47.92,0:02:53.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,南北两极是磁场与地球接触的唯一点
Dialogue: 2,0:02:47.92,0:02:53.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,The north and south poles are the only points where our magnetic field comes into contact with Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.40,0:02:59.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,磁场线与地球大部分表面平行 但向每一极弯曲
Dialogue: 2,0:02:53.40,0:02:59.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,The magnetic field lines run parallel with most of the Earth's surface but curve towards each pole.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:59.61,0:03:02.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,当太阳的带电粒子到达地球时
Dialogue: 2,0:02:59.61,0:03:02.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,When the Sun's charged particles arrive at Earth,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.38,0:03:05.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,它们会被迫沿着磁场线运动
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.38,0:03:05.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,they are forced to travel along the magnetic field lines,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.52,0:03:10.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,导致大部分带电粒子在两极相遇 与地球大气层相互作用
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.52,0:03:10.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,causing most of them to meet at the poles where they interact with Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.41,0:03:15.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,在这一点上 带电粒子可以直接接触到我们的大气层
Dialogue: 2,0:03:10.41,0:03:15.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this point, the charged particles have a direct path through to our atmosphere.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.72,0:03:20.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,磁场中的这个空隙会产生一种被称为“尖端极光”的现象
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.72,0:03:20.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,This gap in our magnetic field creates a phenomenon known as the 'cusp aurora'.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.26,0:03:25.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,借助这一现象 太阳风会在缝隙中被加速
Dialogue: 2,0:03:21.26,0:03:25.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,With cusp auroras, solar winds are accelerated through the gap,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:25.31,0:03:30.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,形成一个具有强烈热能和动能的区域
Dialogue: 2,0:03:25.31,0:03:30.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,creating a very concentrated area with intense heat and kinetic energy.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:30.50,0:03:34.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,当带电粒子与我们大气层中的粒子碰撞时
Dialogue: 2,0:03:30.50,0:03:34.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,As the charged particles collide with the particles in our atmosphere,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:34.59,0:03:41.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,它们会获得足够的能量摆脱地球引力 导致氧气泄漏到太空
Dialogue: 2,0:03:34.59,0:03:41.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,they receive enough energy to escape Earth's gravitational pull, causing streams of oxygen to leak into space.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.36,0:03:46.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,在北极几乎每天晚上都能观测到正常的极光
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.36,0:03:46.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,While a normal aurora can be observed almost every night in the Arctic,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.57,0:03:53.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,而尖端极光只在北极在极夜时的正午时分发生
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.57,0:03:53.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,the cusp aurora only appears at midday when the arctic experiences a full day of darkness.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.79,0:03:55.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,而尖端极光没有固定位置 不断在北极地区移动 导致它更加难以观测
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.79,0:03:55.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,To make it even more difficult to observe,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.89,0:04:01.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,而尖端极光没有固定位置 不断在北极地区移动 导致它更加难以观测
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.89,0:04:01.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,the cusp doesn't have a fixed position and it constantly moves around the Arctic regions.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:02.09,0:04:04.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,但当这些绚丽的极光最终出现的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:04:02.09,0:04:04.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,But when these colorful lights finally appear,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.84,0:04:09.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,就意味着有数百吨的氧气正在逃离地球大气层
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.84,0:04:09.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,it signals that hundreds of tons of oxygen are escaping Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.77,0:04:13.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然每天只能观察到很短的时间
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.77,0:04:13.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although this can only be observed for a short period of time each day,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.97,0:04:17.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这只是实际发生的一小部分
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.97,0:04:17.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,this is only a fraction of what is actually happening.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:17.63,0:04:20.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,当我们在紫外光波段观察地球时
Dialogue: 2,0:04:17.63,0:04:20.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,When we look at the Earth in ultraviolet light,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.28,0:04:24.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们可以发现极光是全天都在发生的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.28,0:04:24.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can see that auroras are constantly happening throughout the day.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.88,0:04:28.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,但地球并不是唯一一个经历极光的星球
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.88,0:04:28.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,But Earth is not the only planet to experience auroras.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.53,0:04:31.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,哈勃太空望远镜通过在紫外波段观察木星
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.53,0:04:31.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Hubble Space Telescope was able to capture
Dialogue: 1,0:04:31.30,0:04:37.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,发现木星上发生了非常类似的极光过程
Dialogue: 2,0:04:31.30,0:04:37.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,a very similar aurora process happening on Jupiter by viewing it in ultraviolet light.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:37.58,0:04:44.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,火星曾经和地球很像 但太阳风在数十亿年来剥蚀了它的大气层
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.58,0:04:44.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Mars used to be a lot like Earth, but the solar wind stripped away its atmosphere over billions of years,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.28,0:04:48.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,留下了遍布星球的小磁场
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.28,0:04:48.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,leaving small magnetic fields dotted around the planet.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.69,0:04:52.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,最终 我们的大气也会经历类似的命运
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.69,0:04:52.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,Eventually, our atmosphere will experience a similar fate.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.96,0:04:57.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,每天 超过100吨的大气会散逸到太空
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.96,0:04:57.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Every day, over 100 tonnes of our atmosphere escapes into space.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:58.24,0:05:04.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,幸运的是 以这个速率 我们的大气层需要数十亿年才能完全消失
Dialogue: 2,0:04:58.24,0:05:04.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, at this rate, it would take billions of years for our atmosphere to completely disappear.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:04.49,0:05:08.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然极光是我们夜空中的众多奇观之一
Dialogue: 2,0:05:04.49,0:05:08.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,And while auroras are one of the many wonders of our night sky,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.88,0:05:15.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,但其背后的原理则是一个振聋发聩的警钟 提醒人类我们的星球是多么脆弱
